{
  "document": {
    "aggregate_severity": {
      "text": "Moderate"
    },
    "category": "csaf_security_advisory",
    "csaf_version": "2.0",
    "notes": [
      {
        "category": "summary",
        "text": "An update is available for gnutls.\nThis update affects Rocky Linux 8.\nA Common Vulnerability Scoring System (CVSS) base score, which gives a detailed severity rating, is available for each vulnerability from the CVE list",
        "title": "Topic"
      },
      {
        "category": "description",
        "text": "The gnutls package provide the GNU Transport Layer Security (GnuTLS) library,\nwhich implements cryptographic algorithms and protocols such as SSL, TLS, and\nDTLS.\n\nThis package update fixes a timing side-channel in deterministic ECDSA.\n\nSecurity Fix(es):\n\n* gnutls: vulnerable to Minerva side-channel information leak (CVE-2024-28834)\n\nFor more details about the security issue(s), including the impact, a CVSS\nscore, acknowledgments, and other related information, refer to the CVE page(s)\nlisted in the References section.\n\nThis advisory is provided by Ctrl IQ, Inc for Rocky Linux systems. For more information about CIQ security practices, visit https://ciq.com/security.",
        "title": "Description"
      }
    ],
    "publisher": {
